<p><strong>What does the winning mindset feel like?</strong></p>

<p>â€¨â€¨A winning mindsetÂ is tied to an identity and worldview. Losing isnâ€™t just an event which is disappointing - it conflicts with who you are.Â  When you lose, you are not being yourself. Your entire worldview is at threat.  They do not care for what other people think, but care much more about what they think of themselves.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>â€œShow me a good loser, and Iâ€™ll show you a loserâ€.Â </p>
</blockquote>

<ul>
  <li>A supreme, unwavering confidence in their abilities. There are no seeds of self-doubt ready to sprout.</li>
  <li>A laser-like focus when surrounded by distractions and a refusal to think of things outside their control. The focus conquers all anxiety, frustration, and discouragement.</li>
  <li>Ability to bring intensity to the next level at the right moments. Especially in the face of adversity (e.g. red card, missed chance, goal down), winners give everything theyâ€™ve got in order to win.  Since winners bring their A-game in every task, it is crucial to pick battles.
